<tr>
    <td  bgcolor="#000080"><FONT color="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;Subject:&nbsp;Leatherfoot Raider Skullcap Quest</font></td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td  bgcolor="#DCDCDC" valign="TOP"><table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" border="0">
<tr>
    <td  bgcolor="#DCDCDC" width="100%" valign="top"><tt><font color="#000000">
Author:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:&#106;&#106;&#99;&#104;&#105;&#112;&#109;&#97;&#110;&#64;&#101;&#97;&#114;&#116;&#104;&#108;&#105;&#110;&#107;&#46;&#110;&#101;&#116;?subject=Leatherfoot Raider Skullcap Quest">Undertall</a>&nbsp;(sdn-ar-006wimilwP331.dialsprint.net)<br>
Date:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;08-23-2000 18:23<br><br>
This is the accurate information for this quest from a newly ordained Leatherfoot Raider. I have recently completed this quest and the information that follows is tested and successful as I am now wearing my Leatherfoot Raider Skullcap. <BR>
This quest originates in the Halfling city of Rivervale with Marshall Aubrey who is found on the top floor of the bank building in one of the alcoves. Hail him and ask him the questions with the bracketed key words. He will ask you where you are from ( I think this may have to do with who can wear the cap because I told him "Rivervale" and my cap is for a halfling only). He will request the following 4 items from you.<BR>
<BR>
Grizzly Bear Skin- Found in North Karana on the Grizzly Bears or a bit less frequently in West Commons from a Young Kodiak or Kodiak.<BR>
<BR>
Polar Bear Skin- Found on the Polar Bears in Everfrost<BR>
<BR>
Alligator Skin- Found on a fat alligator in the Innothule Swamp. I got mine near the entrance/tunnel to South Ro<BR>
<BR>
Shark Skin- can be obtained off either of the 2 sharks found near the rocks just off the docks in East Freeport.*note* I have seen many questions as to whether you need the stackable or lore (non-stackable) skin. I was successful using ONE of the STACKABLE type skin.<BR>
<BR>
Give these all to him at the SAME TIME and he will give you exp, some gold and a cap with stats of 4AC and +10 CHA.<BR>
<BR>
In order to receive the genuine Leatherfoot Raider cap however you must give him the cap back with a Dragoon Dirk AT THE SAME TIME. This will reward you with a exp, 2pp and a Leatherfoot Raider Skullcap cap with the following stats: <BR>
7AC +5STR, +5AGI, +10CHA, +5 Sv Vs Magic and 1 Charge of a Ring of Commons teleport. <BR>
<BR>
The Quest is easliy accomplished at level 13+ (I did mine at 16 and everything conned low blue or green to me) but the Dragoon Dirk is a higher level drop (level 25+) so if you want the cap at this level, the best thing to do is buy the dirk. I have seen them for sale in Oasis, West Commons and East Commons for around 25-50pp.<BR>
<BR>
Most complaints about this quest seem to stem from the low frequency of the alligator skin drop. I got mine from the first fat alligator I killed (luck?) while some have said it took them 25+. All I can say is just keep at it, it will be there. Many of the skins (with possibly the exception of the alligator) can also be purchased from merchants in the areas they are found in as they are generally not worth much to most other players.<BR>
<BR>
Area tips: Stay away from the Dark Elf that spawns on the wall in the East Freeport dock area near the sharks. I was KOS to her and she is lev 15-17. If you stay out where the sharks are, she won't bother you. (She seems to have about about a 20' aggro area). Also in the Innothule swamp, don't venture to far from the zone if you are lower level as the Kobolds will gang up on you and there is a NPC trollslayer wandering around who conned green to me at 16 but killed me fairly easily with 20 point damage double attacks.<BR>
<BR>
Have fun! The quest requires a bit of travel but for those of you who like to earn your items, this one certainly is rewarding!<BR>
<BR>
Underall &lt;Dark Renaissance&gt;<BR>
Level 18 Halfling Druid<BR>
Seventh Hammer Server<BR>
</font></tt></td>
</tr>
